CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1958, page 1, reads: "Sleuths Quiz Robber-Killer - City detectives are shown as they questioned 19-year-old Walter Phillips, second from right, forefront, about the robbery and murder of 80-year-old Green Evans, from a prominent Garfield Hill family. Left to right: Lieut. of Detectives Ray O'Toole, Homicide Detectives Fred Del Cimmuto, William Best and J. Kieran Jennings, far right, showing Phillips the statement which he signed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, left to right: Lieutenant of Detectives, Ray O'Toole; Homicide Detectives, Fred Del Cimmuto, William Best, and J. Kieran Jennings holding statement in front of Walter Phillips in office interior
